{
  "texts": [
    "It can be purely a matter of vision, and frequently aligned with image.",
    "As material, embodied, and cognitive processes, text and speech could hardly be more different (Bezemer and Kress 2016, Halliday 1987[2002], Ong 1992) (Kalantzis and Cope 2022).",
    "This is why literacy is so important and so challenging for learners, not to be trivialized by reduction to simplistic handful of sound-letter transliterations.",
    "It's much, much harder than that.The phonics advocates are right about this much: it's a good thing to call out explicitly key patterns in the meaning making process.",
    "In the limited time for learning in school, this is more efficient than immersion models."
  ]
}